{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"994e5122-b4e3-42a5-a687-b0da8cebc5ac","content":"MSTest v3 dropped support for `.testsettings` files. Here's what I did:\n\n**Created `local.runsettings`** — the modern replacement:\n- **`<TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>`** — preserves your 30-second timeout.\n- **`<DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled>`** — the old `AssemblyResolution` / `useLoadContext` setting is no longer needed; modern MSTest loads assemblies in-place by default.\n\n**Updated `TestProject.csproj`** to auto-use the new runsettings file via `<RunSettingsFilePath>`.\n\nYou can safely delete `local.testsettings` once you've verified tests run correctly. If you prefer per-test timeouts instead of a global one, you can also use the `[Timeout(30000)]` attribute on individual test methods or classes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"26145fbf-ccae-4f1a-8b91-301464a74e18","outputTokens":209},"id":"a39e42cd-c9b7-4f36-a6fb-ec09571d8a7d","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:02:16.663Z","parentId":"c1019a85-7869-42e3-befd-d28f81b925b4"}
